    Data, DataListener, DataMap<String,DataSeries<?>>, DataTable, TableView, View, Iterable<DataRow>

    public class SortedTable
extends AbstractTableView<SeriesViewRow<?>,DataTable>
    Creates a view of a table containing the rows in the table sorted according to the natural ordering of the values in a specified series or according to a provided Comparator that defines an ordering over the DataRows in the table.
    Author:
    O. J. Coleman

    • Constructor Detail

      • SortedTable

        public SortedTable(DataTable input,
                   int sortingSeries)

        Create a view of the given table containing the rows in the table sorted into ascending order, according to the natural ordering of the values in the specified series.

        All values in the specified series must implement the Comparable interface. Furthermore, all values must be mutually comparable (that is, v1.compareTo(v2) must not throw a ClassCastException for any values v1 and v2).

        This sort is guaranteed to be stable: equal values will not be reordered as a result of the sort.

      • SortedTable

      • SortedTable

        public SortedTable(DataTable input,
                   Comparator<DataRow> comparator)

        Create a view of this table containing the rows in this table sorted according to the order induced by the specified comparator. The comparator must accept any two DataRows from this table and determine their relative ordering according to the contract specified by Comparator

        This sort is guaranteed to be stable: equal rows, according to the comparator, will not be reordered as a result of the sort.
